Content:: Ashok Madansingh Jagdale (20 November 1945 – 25 July 2022)[1] was an Indian cricketer who played for Madhya Pradesh.[2] He was a right-hand batsman who bowled right-arm medium-fast. He was the son of Madhavsinh Jagdale and elder brother of Sanjay Jagdale.  This biographical article related to an Indian cricket person born in the 1940s is a stub.
